parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the airbag inflator can cause metal fragments to pass through the airbag and into the vehicle interior, resulting in injury or death to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
potential for airbag deployment failure
potential for metal fragments to cause injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
and error messages appear on the dashboard
such as "Service Traction Control
" "Service Stabilitrak
" and "Engine Power Reduced."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
and error messages appear on the dashboard
such as "Service Airbag."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of an accident by reducing the visibility of the vehicle to other drivers.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function
and error messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can reduce the visibility of important information, such as speed and tire pressure, increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The dashboard lights and displays do not function
and error messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Side Blind Zone Detection System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side blind zone detection system can increase the risk of an accident by reducing the visibility of other vehicles in the blind spot.
symptoms: The side blind zone detection system does not function
and error messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuse block/box can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
and error messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabiltrak/Traction Control system can cause the vehicle to lose power, reducing speed to 20-25 mph, and may lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The Stabiltrak/Traction Control warning lights illuminate
the vehicle slows down or loses power
the engine light turns on
and the vehicle may jerk or shake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine light turns on
the vehicle loses power
and the speed is reduced to 20-25 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch or transmission system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
